page.title: 09West End
page.content:
{West End}is a small hamlet of about twenty houses. It is about one mile from both Waltham St. Lawrence and Shurlock Row. The{village school}is in West End. It was built to replace two small schools in the villages and had to be built in between the two to stop arguments. When it was built there were only about three houses in West End.
West End has a{post box}and a{ {telephone box}. Near the hamlet is{ {Woods Yard}which is a very large{Do it {yourself and timber yard}. People visit the yard from many miles away and are always having to ask the way there.
There are{floods}on most of the roads in West End every winter.
